<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10483098>
    dc:description "Fig. 1. Phylogenetic analysis of prenyltransferases from C. sativa. The eight putative CsPTs identified in the C. sativa genome were aligned with the amino acid sequences of various plant aromatic prenyltransferases that have been previously identified using Clustal W and a Neighbor-joining phylogenetic tree (1000 replicates) to illustrate their evolutionary relationships was then constructed using the MEGA 6.0 software package. Bootstrap values (> 60%) are indicated at the nodes of each branch and the branch lengths are proportional to the number of amino acid substitutions per sequence. The sequences and species abbreviations for all of these prenyltransferases are listed in Supplemental Fig. S1 along with their corresponding GenBank accession numbers. Note that the eight CsPTs (bolded) distinctly fall into three groups, which are involved in either tocopherol (II), plastoquinone (V), or terpenophenolic (VI) biosynthesis." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10483098/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

